3. Steps to Configure Telnet in Cisco Packet Tracer
• Step 1: Assign IP Address:
Router> enable
Router# configure terminal
Router(config)# interface fastEthernet 0/0
Router(config-if)# ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0
Router(config-if)# no shutdown
• Step 2: Set VTY Password:
Router(config)# line vty 0 4
Router(config-line)# password cisco
Router(config-line)# login

• Step 3: Set Enable Password:
Router(config)# enable password class
• Step 4 (Optional): Create Local User:
Router(config)# username admin password admin123
Router(config)# line vty 0 4
Router(config-line)# login local

• Step 5: Test Connection:
On PC → Command Prompt:
ping 192.168.1.1
telnet 192.168.1.1
Enter username/password → Access router CLI remotely.
